@startuml ssd-cache-coherence
' Mid-query consistency: a query is mid-search on v1 when v2's catalog
' update lands. The POSIX unlink-with-open-fd guarantee lets the in-flight
' query complete against v1's bytes; the next query lands on v2.

title Mid-query consistency: v2 lands while a v1 query is in flight

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "client A\n(early query)" as a
actor "client B\n(later query)" as b
participant "query_dp" as dp
participant "shard_tier\n(SSD)" as tier
participant "kernel\n(VFS + page cache)" as kern
participant "_SHARD_CACHE\n(RAM)" as ram
database "shard_catalog\n(Postgres)" as catalog
participant "index_builder" as builder

== t=0 ms: client A starts a query against v1 ==

a -> dp : POST /v1/query
activate dp
dp -> catalog : list_shards
catalog --> dp : v1 (newest)
dp -> ram : _cache_get(shard_id_v1)
ram --> dp : HIT (FAISS handle + sidecar)
dp -> kern : index.search() begins\n(holds open fd on v1 file)
note right of dp #LightBlue
  v1's open file descriptor pins the
  inode. Even an unlink during this
  search leaves the bytes addressable
  via the existing mapping.
end note

== t=20 ms: builder publishes v2 ==

builder -> catalog : INSERT v2; NOTIFY catalog_updates
note over builder, catalog #LightYellow
  Same transaction. NOTIFY fires
  on commit; lost on rollback.
end note
catalog -> dp : LISTEN delivers {shard_id_v2}
dp -> dp : invalidate cached list_shards\nfor (tenant, dataset)
note right of dp
  v1's _cache_get entry is NOT touched.
  v1's SSD-tier file is NOT unlinked yet.
  Invalidation only affects the next
  list_shards call.
end note

== t=40 ms: client A's search completes against v1 ==

kern --> dp : pages from v1 inode
dp -> dp : map hits via v1 sidecar
dp --> a : results from v1
deactivate dp

note over a, dp #LightBlue
  Client A sees v1 results.
  Within-query consistency holds.
end note

== t=50 ms: SSD tier may evict v1 (W-TinyLFU decision) ==

tier -> tier : eviction check
alt v1 is the LRU end AND age >= MIN_RESIDENT_S
  tier -> kern : unlink v1 file
  note right of tier
    Unlink is safe. Any open fd on
    v1 (none after t=40 ms) keeps the
    inode alive; future opens fail.
  end note
else v1 is not the LRU end yet
  note right of tier
    v1 stays on SSD. Future queries
    against v1's shard_id still find it,
    but no query path resolves v1 as
    "newest" anymore.
  end note
end

== t=100 ms: client B's query ==

b -> dp : POST /v1/query
activate dp
dp -> catalog : list_shards
catalog --> dp : v2 (newest), v1
dp -> ram : _cache_get(shard_id_v2)
ram --> dp : MISS
dp -> tier : shard_tier.fetch(shard_id_v2, v2_uri)
activate tier
tier -> tier : GET v2 + write file
tier --> dp : local_path for v2
deactivate tier
dp -> kern : faiss.read_index(v2, IO_FLAG_MMAP)
dp -> kern : index.search()
kern --> dp : pages from v2
dp --> b : results from v2
deactivate dp

note over a, b #LightBlue
  Client A: v1 result (consistent, complete).
  Client B: v2 result (the now-current version).
  Between-query consistency is intentionally
  eventual; within-query consistency is strict.
end note

@enduml
